29#define gf100_clk(p) container_of((p), struct gf100_clk, base)
30#include "priv.h"
31#include "pll.h"

33#include <subdev/bios.h>
34#include <subdev/bios/pll.h>
35#include <subdev/timer.h>
36
37struct gf100_clk_info {
38 u32 freq;
39 u32 ssel;
40 u32 mdiv;
41 u32 dsrc;
42 u32 ddiv;
43 u32 coef;
44};
45
46struct gf100_clk {
47 struct nvkm_clk base;
48 struct gf100_clk_info eng[16];
49};
50
51static u32 read_div(struct gf100_clk *, int, u32, u32);
52
53static u32
54read_vco(struct gf100_clk *clk, u32 dsrc)
55{
56 struct nvkm_device *device = clk->base.subdev.device;
57 u32 ssrc = nvkm_rd32(device, dsrc);
58 if (!(ssrc & 0x00000100))
59 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_sppll0);
60 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_sppll1);
61}
62
63static u32
64read_pll(struct gf100_clk *clk, u32 pll)
65{
66 struct nvkm_device *device = clk->base.subdev.device;
67 u32 ctrl = nvkm_rd32(device, pll + 0x00);
68 u32 coef = nvkm_rd32(device, pll + 0x04);
69 u32 P = (coef & 0x003f0000) >> 16;
70 u32 N = (coef & 0x0000ff00) >> 8;
71 u32 M = (coef & 0x000000ff) >> 0;
72 u32 sclk;
73
74 if (!(ctrl & 0x00000001))
75 return 0;
76
77 switch (pll) {
78 case 0x00e800:
79 case 0x00e820:
80 sclk = device->crystal;
81 P = 1;
82 break;
83 case 0x132000:
84 sclk = nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_mpllsrc);
85 break;
86 case 0x132020:
87 sclk = nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_mpllsrcref);
88 break;
89 case 0x137000:
90 case 0x137020:
91 case 0x137040:
92 case 0x1370e0:
93 sclk = read_div(clk, (pll & 0xff) / 0x20, 0x137120, 0x137140);
94 break;
95 default:
96 return 0;
97 }
98
99 return sclk * N / M / P;
100}
101
102static u32
103read_div(struct gf100_clk *clk, int doff, u32 dsrc, u32 dctl)
104{
105 struct nvkm_device *device = clk->base.subdev.device;
106 u32 ssrc = nvkm_rd32(device, dsrc + (doff * 4));
107 u32 sctl = nvkm_rd32(device, dctl + (doff * 4));
108
109 switch (ssrc & 0x00000003) {
110 case 0:
111 if ((ssrc & 0x00030000) != 0x00030000)
112 return device->crystal;
113 return 108000;
114 case 2:
115 return 100000;
116 case 3:
117 if (sctl & 0x80000000) {
118 u32 sclk = read_vco(clk, dsrc + (doff * 4));
119 u32 sdiv = (sctl & 0x0000003f) + 2;
120 return (sclk * 2) / sdiv;
121 }
122
123 return read_vco(clk, dsrc + (doff * 4));
124 default:
125 return 0;
126 }
127}
128
129static u32
130read_clk(struct gf100_clk *clk, int idx)
131{
132 struct nvkm_device *device = clk->base.subdev.device;
133 u32 sctl = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x137250 + (idx * 4));
134 u32 ssel = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x137100);
135 u32 sclk, sdiv;
136
137 if (ssel & (1 << idx)) {
138 if (idx < 7)
139 sclk = read_pll(clk, 0x137000 + (idx * 0x20));
140 else
141 sclk = read_pll(clk, 0x1370e0);
142 sdiv = ((sctl & 0x00003f00) >> 8) + 2;
143 } else {
144 sclk = read_div(clk, idx, 0x137160, 0x1371d0);
145 sdiv = ((sctl & 0x0000003f) >> 0) + 2;
146 }
147
148 if (sctl & 0x80000000)
149 return (sclk * 2) / sdiv;
150
151 return sclk;
152}
153
154static int
155gf100_clk_read(struct nvkm_clk *base, enum nv_clk_src src)
156{
157 struct gf100_clk *clk = gf100_clk(base);
158 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &clk->base.subdev;
159 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
160
161 switch (src) {
162 case nv_clk_src_crystal:
163 return device->crystal;
164 case nv_clk_src_href:
165 return 100000;
166 case nv_clk_src_sppll0:
167 return read_pll(clk, 0x00e800);
168 case nv_clk_src_sppll1:
169 return read_pll(clk, 0x00e820);
170
171 case nv_clk_src_mpllsrcref:
172 return read_div(clk, 0, 0x137320, 0x137330);
173 case nv_clk_src_mpllsrc:
174 return read_pll(clk, 0x132020);
175 case nv_clk_src_mpll:
176 return read_pll(clk, 0x132000);
177 case nv_clk_src_mdiv:
178 return read_div(clk, 0, 0x137300, 0x137310);
179 case nv_clk_src_mem:
180 if (nvkm_rd32(device, 0x1373f0) & 0x00000002)
181 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_mpll);
182 return nvkm_clk_read(&clk->base, nv_clk_src_mdiv);
183
184 case nv_clk_src_gpc:
185 return read_clk(clk, 0x00);
186 case nv_clk_src_rop:
187 return read_clk(clk, 0x01);
188 case nv_clk_src_hubk07:
189 return read_clk(clk, 0x02);
190 case nv_clk_src_hubk06:
191 return read_clk(clk, 0x07);
192 case nv_clk_src_hubk01:
193 return read_clk(clk, 0x08);
194 case nv_clk_src_copy:
195 return read_clk(clk, 0x09);
196 case nv_clk_src_daemon:
197 return read_clk(clk, 0x0c);
198 case nv_clk_src_vdec:
199 return read_clk(clk, 0x0e);
200 default:
201 nvkm_error(subdev, "invalid clock source %d\n", src);
202 return -EINVAL;
203 }
204}
205
206static u32
207calc_div(struct gf100_clk *clk, int idx, u32 ref, u32 freq, u32 *ddiv)
208{
209 u32 div = min((ref * 2) / freq, (u32)65);
210 if (div < 2)
211 div = 2;
212
213 *ddiv = div - 2;
214 return (ref * 2) / div;
215}
216
217static u32
218calc_src(struct gf100_clk *clk, int idx, u32 freq, u32 *dsrc, u32 *ddiv)
219{
220 u32 sclk;
221
222 /* use one of the fixed frequencies if possible */
223 *ddiv = 0x00000000;
224 switch (freq) {
225 case 27000:
226 case 108000:
227 *dsrc = 0x00000000;
228 if (freq == 108000)
229 *dsrc |= 0x00030000;
230 return freq;
231 case 100000:
232 *dsrc = 0x00000002;
233 return freq;
234 default:
235 *dsrc = 0x00000003;
236 break;
237 }
238
239 /* otherwise, calculate the closest divider */
240 sclk = read_vco(clk, 0x137160 + (idx * 4));
241 if (idx < 7)
242 sclk = calc_div(clk, idx, sclk, freq, ddiv);
243 return sclk;
244}
245
246static u32
247calc_pll(struct gf100_clk *clk, int idx, u32 freq, u32 *coef)
248{
249 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &clk->base.subdev;
250 struct nvkm_bios *bios = subdev->device->bios;
251 struct nvbios_pll limits;
252 int N, M, P, ret;
253
254 ret = nvbios_pll_parse(bios, 0x137000 + (idx * 0x20), &limits);
255 if (ret)
256 return 0;
257
258 limits.refclk = read_div(clk, idx, 0x137120, 0x137140);
259 if (!limits.refclk)
260 return 0;
261
262 ret = gt215_pll_calc(subdev, &limits, freq, &N, NULL, &M, &P);
263 if (ret <= 0)
264 return 0;
265
266 *coef = (P << 16) | (N << 8) | M;
267 return ret;
268}
269
270static int
271calc_clk(struct gf100_clk *clk, struct nvkm_cstate *cstate, int idx, int dom)
272{
273 struct gf100_clk_info *info = &clk->eng[idx];
274 u32 freq = cstate->domain[dom];
275 u32 src0, div0, div1D, div1P = 0;
276 u32 clk0, clk1 = 0;
277
278 /* invalid clock domain */
279 if (!freq)
280 return 0;
281
282 /* first possible path, using only dividers */
283 clk0 = calc_src(clk, idx, freq, &src0, &div0);
284 clk0 = calc_div(clk, idx, clk0, freq, &div1D);
285
286 /* see if we can get any closer using PLLs */
287 if (clk0 != freq && (0x00004387 & (1 << idx))) {
288 if (idx <= 7)
289 clk1 = calc_pll(clk, idx, freq, &info->coef);
290 else
291 clk1 = cstate->domain[nv_clk_src_hubk06];
292 clk1 = calc_div(clk, idx, clk1, freq, &div1P);
293 }
294
295 /* select the method which gets closest to target freq */
296 if (abs((int)freq - clk0) <= abs((int)freq - clk1)) {
297 info->dsrc = src0;
298 if (div0) {
299 info->ddiv |= 0x80000000;
300 info->ddiv |= div0 << 8;
301 info->ddiv |= div0;
302 }
303 if (div1D) {
304 info->mdiv |= 0x80000000;
305 info->mdiv |= div1D;
306 }
307 info->ssel = info->coef = 0;
308 info->freq = clk0;
309 } else {
310 if (div1P) {
311 info->mdiv |= 0x80000000;
312 info->mdiv |= div1P << 8;
313 }
314 info->ssel = (1 << idx);
315 info->freq = clk1;
316 }
317
318 return 0;
319}
320
321static int
322gf100_clk_calc(struct nvkm_clk *base, struct nvkm_cstate *cstate)
323{
324 struct gf100_clk *clk = gf100_clk(base);
325 int ret;
326
327 if ((ret = calc_clk(clk, cstate, 0x00, nv_clk_src_gpc)) ||
328 (ret = calc_clk(clk, cstate, 0x01, nv_clk_src_rop)) ||
329 (ret = calc_clk(clk, cstate, 0x02, nv_clk_src_hubk07)) ||
330 (ret = calc_clk(clk, cstate, 0x07, nv_clk_src_hubk06)) ||
331 (ret = calc_clk(clk, cstate, 0x08, nv_clk_src_hubk01)) ||
332 (ret = calc_clk(clk, cstate, 0x09, nv_clk_src_copy)) ||
333 (ret = calc_clk(clk, cstate, 0x0c, nv_clk_src_daemon)) ||
334 (ret = calc_clk(clk, cstate, 0x0e, nv_clk_src_vdec)))
335 return ret;
336
337 return 0;
338}
339
340static void
341gf100_clk_prog_0(struct gf100_clk *clk, int idx)
342{
343 struct gf100_clk_info *info = &clk->eng[idx];
344 struct nvkm_device *device = clk->base.subdev.device;
345 if (idx < 7 && !info->ssel) {
346 nvkm_mask(device, 0x1371d0 + (idx * 0x04), 0x80003f3f, info->ddiv);
347 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x137160 + (idx * 0x04), info->dsrc);
348 }
349}
350
351static void
352gf100_clk_prog_1(struct gf100_clk *clk, int idx)
353{
354 struct nvkm_device *device = clk->base.subdev.device;
355 nvkm_mask(device, 0x137100, (1 << idx), 0x00000000);
356 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
357 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x137100) & (1 << idx)))
358 break;
359 );
360}
361
362static void
363gf100_clk_prog_2(struct gf100_clk *clk, int idx)
364{
365 struct gf100_clk_info *info = &clk->eng[idx];
366 struct nvkm_device *device = clk->base.subdev.device;
367 const u32 addr = 0x137000 + (idx * 0x20);
368 if (idx <= 7) {
369 nvkm_mask(device, addr + 0x00, 0x00000004, 0x00000000);
370 nvkm_mask(device, addr + 0x00, 0x00000001, 0x00000000);
371 if (info->coef) {
372 nvkm_wr32(device, addr + 0x04, info->coef);
373 nvkm_mask(device, addr + 0x00, 0x00000001, 0x00000001);
374 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
375 if (nvkm_rd32(device, addr + 0x00) & 0x00020000)
376 break;
377 );
378 nvkm_mask(device, addr + 0x00, 0x00020004, 0x00000004);
379 }
380 }
381}
382
383static void
384gf100_clk_prog_3(struct gf100_clk *clk, int idx)
385{
386 struct gf100_clk_info *info = &clk->eng[idx];
387 struct nvkm_device *device = clk->base.subdev.device;
388 if (info->ssel) {
389 nvkm_mask(device, 0x137100, (1 << idx), info->ssel);
390 nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
391 u32 tmp = nvkm_rd32(device, 0x137100) & (1 << idx);
392 if (tmp == info->ssel)
393 break;
394 );
395 }
396}
397
398static void
399gf100_clk_prog_4(struct gf100_clk *clk, int idx)
400{
401 struct gf100_clk_info *info = &clk->eng[idx];
402 struct nvkm_device *device = clk->base.subdev.device;
403 nvkm_mask(device, 0x137250 + (idx * 0x04), 0x00003f3f, info->mdiv);
404}
405
406static int
407gf100_clk_prog(struct nvkm_clk *base)
408{
409 struct gf100_clk *clk = gf100_clk(base);
410 struct {
411 void (*exec)(struct gf100_clk *, int);
412 } stage[] = {
413 { gf100_clk_prog_0 }, /* div programming */
414 { gf100_clk_prog_1 }, /* select div mode */
415 { gf100_clk_prog_2 }, /* (maybe) program pll */
416 { gf100_clk_prog_3 }, /* (maybe) select pll mode */
417 { gf100_clk_prog_4 }, /* final divider */
418 };
419 int i, j;
420
421 for (i = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(stage); i++) {
422 for (j = 0; j < ARRAY_SIZE(clk->eng); j++) {
423 if (!clk->eng[j].freq)
424 continue;
425 stage[i].exec(clk, j);
426 }
427 }
428
429 return 0;
430}
431
432static void
433gf100_clk_tidy(struct nvkm_clk *base)
434{
435 struct gf100_clk *clk = gf100_clk(base);
436 memset(clk->eng, 0x00, sizeof(clk->eng));
437}
438
439static const struct nvkm_clk_func
440gf100_clk = {
441 .read = gf100_clk_read,
442 .calc = gf100_clk_calc,
443 .prog = gf100_clk_prog,
444 .tidy = gf100_clk_tidy,
445 .domains = {
446 { nv_clk_src_crystal, 0xff },
447 { nv_clk_src_href , 0xff },
448 { nv_clk_src_hubk06 , 0x00 },
449 { nv_clk_src_hubk01 , 0x01 },
450 { nv_clk_src_copy , 0x02 },
451 { nv_clk_src_gpc , 0x03, 0, "core", 2000 },
452 { nv_clk_src_rop , 0x04 },
453 { nv_clk_src_mem , 0x05, 0, "memory", 1000 },
454 { nv_clk_src_vdec , 0x06 },
455 { nv_clk_src_daemon , 0x0a },
456 { nv_clk_src_hubk07 , 0x0b },
457 { nv_clk_src_max }
458 }
459};
460
461int
462gf100_clk_new(struct nvkm_device *device, int index, struct nvkm_clk **pclk)
463{
464 struct gf100_clk *clk;
465
466 if (!(clk = kzalloc(sizeof(*clk), GFP_KERNEL)))
467 return -ENOMEM;
468 *pclk = &clk->base;
469
470 return nvkm_clk_ctor(&gf100_clk, device, index, false, &clk->base);
471}
